# Release Notes - Version 0.0.43

**Release Date:** August 3, 2025  
**Status:** Production Ready

## 🐛 Critical Bug Fixes

### Type Mismatch Issues Resolved
This release addresses critical type hint mismatches that were causing fatal errors and Internal Server Errors across the application.

#### Container Type Fixes
- **BayanServiceProvider**: Fixed import from `IslamWiki\Core\Asas` to `IslamWiki\Core\Container\Asas`
- **All Controllers**: Updated constructor type hints to use `\IslamWiki\Core\Container\Asas`
- **Service Providers**: Ensured consistent container type usage throughout

#### Session Manager Type Fixes
- **SessionManager vs Wisal**: Resolved type mismatches between non-existent `SessionManager` and actual `Wisal` implementation
- **Controllers**: Updated `DashboardController`, `ProfileController`, `SettingsController`
- **Middleware**: Fixed `AuthenticationMiddleware`, `CsrfMiddleware`
- **Auth System**: Updated `AuthManager`, `IslamicAuthController`

### Files Modified
- `src/Providers/BayanServiceProvider.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/Controller.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/HomeController.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/PageController.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/SearchController.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/IqraSearchController.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/IslamicContentController.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/ProfileController.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/DashboardController.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/CommunityController.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/ConfigurationController.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/SettingsController.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/CacheController.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/SecurityController.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/QueueController.php`
- `src/Http/Middleware/AuthenticationMiddleware.php`
- `src/Http/Middleware/CsrfMiddleware.php`
- `src/Core/Auth/AuthManager.php`
- `src/Http/Controllers/Auth/IslamicAuthController.php`

## 🔧 Technical Improvements

### Type Safety
- All container type hints now consistently use `\IslamWiki\Core\Container\Asas`
- All session manager type hints now use `Wisal` (the actual implementation)
- Improved dependency injection consistency
- Enhanced error handling and logging

### Code Quality
- Updated all use statements and docblocks for consistency
- Maintained backward compatibility while fixing type safety issues
- Resolved fatal errors related to type mismatches in service providers
- Fixed Internal Server Errors caused by incorrect type hints

## 🚀 Impact

### Before This Release
- Fatal errors when accessing pages due to type mismatches
- Internal Server Errors in controllers and middleware
- Inconsistent type hints across the codebase
- Service provider registration failures

### After This Release
- All pages load without type-related errors
- Consistent type safety throughout the application
- Proper dependency injection working correctly
- Enhanced stability and reliability

